Malusi Gigaba's legal counsel is adamant that the former minister's estranged wife Norma Mngoma cannot be forced to appear before the Zondo Commission. Mngoma initially volunteered to take the witness stand but withdrew at the eleventh hour. She has now been issued with a summons to testify. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo has ruled that Norma Mngoma must testify in public. Mngoma was initially expected to testify earlier this month, but withdrew at the last minute. This prompted Deputy Chief Justice Zondo to issue her with a summons. READ: LIVESTREAM: Zondo Commission hears Gigaba's application for leave to cross-examine ex wife Mngoma is widely expected to speak about Gigaba's relationship with the controversial Gupta family. Watch the video above for more details on the story